verses.verse: To the chief <WH5329> Musician <WH5329> on Neginoth, <WH5058> A Psalm <WH4210> or Song. <WH7892> God <WH430> be merciful <WH2603> to us, and bless <WH1288> us; and cause his face <WH6440> to shine <WH215> on us; Selah. <WH5542>
That your way <WH1870> may be known <WH3045> on earth, <WH776> your saving <WH3444> health <WH3444> among all <WH3605> nations. <WH1471>
Let the people <WH5971> praise <WH3034> you, O God; <WH430> let all <WH3605> the people <WH5971> praise <WH3034> you.

O let the nations <WH3816> be glad <WH8056> and sing <WH7442> for joy: for you shall judge <WH8199> the people <WH5971> righteously, <WH4334> and govern <WH5148> the nations <WH3816> on earth. <WH776> Selah. <WH5542>
Let the people <WH5971> praise <WH3034> you, O God; <WH430> let all <WH3605> the people <WH5971> praise <WH3034> you.
Then shall the earth <WH776> yield <WH5414> her increase; <WH2981> and God, <WH430> even our own God, <WH430> shall bless <WH1288> us.
God <WH430> shall bless <WH1288> us; and all <WH3605> the ends <WH657> of the earth <WH776> shall fear <WH3372> him.
